article.description: — Frankie Fidler had 28 points in Omaha's 79-72 victory against Idaho on Sunday night.
article.headline: Fidler puts up 28, Omaha knocks off Idaho 79-72
article.linkText: Fidler puts up 28, Omaha knocks off Idaho 79-72
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. -- — Frankie Fidler had 28 points in Omaha's 79-72 victory against Idaho on Sunday night. Fidler added 11 rebounds for the Mavericks (1-2). Marquel Sutton scored 16 points and added eight rebounds. Dylan Brougham recorded nine points and finished 4 of 6 from the floor. The Vandals (1-2) were led in scoring by Divant'e Moffitt, who finished with 29 points. Yusef Salih added 13 points for Idaho. In addition, Nigel Burris finished with 10 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
